# Trinity Protocol v3.3.1 — UCI Data Integration (V6 Base)

Upgrade the "V6: Pseudo-Labeling Boost" script to incorporate the UCI dataset ([heart_disease_uci.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/heart_disease_uci.csv)) as ground-truth training data.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The UCI dataset uses natural language labels (e.g., "typical angina", "male") while the competition data uses codes (e.g., "TA", "M"). 
> I am implementing a `map_uci_to_s6e1` function to normalize these before training.

## Proposed Changes

### [heart_top5_v3_3_uci.py](file:///home/kizabgd/heart_top5_v3_3_uci.py)

#### [NEW]
- **Base Logic**: Port the OOF/Pseudo-labeling pipeline from the provided V6 snippet.
- **UCI Loader**:
    - Load [heart_disease_uci.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/heart_disease_uci.csv).
    - Map `sex` (Male/Female -> M/F).
    - Map `cp` (typical angina -> TA, etc.).
    - Map `rest_ecg` (normal -> Normal, etc.).
    - Map `slope` (up -> Up, down -> Down, flat -> Flat).
    - Map `target` (Presence/Absence or 0/1 -> 0/1).
- **Expansion**: Concatenate mapped UCI data to the competition `train` dataframe before the first training pass.
- **Feature Engineering**: Apply the "Domain Features" and "Log/Interactions" from the V6 snippet.

